1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,022
We need to define axioms to determine the behaviour of this edge

2
00:00:04,122 --> 00:00:08,918
relation E. Without any axioms, every possible combination of points and all

3
00:00:09,018 --> 00:00:13,170
possible arrows drawn between them is a model of our empty theory.

4
00:00:13,266 --> 00:00:16,756
An axiom can be any First Order Logic sentence. For

5
00:00:16,856 --> 00:00:21,473
example, we can consider this formula phi, expressing transitivity,

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:24,244
meaning that if there is some path between nodes,

7
00:00:24,344 --> 00:00:26,933
then there is a direct path between these nodes.

8
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:33,015
Or this sentence psi expressing irreflexivity, which enforces that any

9
00:00:33,115 --> 00:00:37,071
model of it must not contain any self-referential arrows.

10
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,495
We can combine the sentences, and consider the collection

11
00:00:40,595 --> 00:00:43,415
of all structures which satisfy both phi and psi,

12
00:00:43,515 --> 00:00:47,287
i.e. the collection of all transitive and irreflexive structures.

13
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:51,358
In general, given any collection of sentences Sigma, this is the

14
00:00:51,458 --> 00:00:54,516
model set of Sigma, and it is the set of possible

15
00:00:54,616 --> 00:00:58,126
structures which satisfy each of the sentences in Sigma.

16
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:02,844
Note that if Sigma contains an unsatisfiable sentence, such as x

17
00:01:02,944 --> 00:01:06,328
does not equal x, then Mod Sigma will be empty.

18
00:01:06,466 --> 00:01:10,698
And the soundness of First order logic, tells us that if our set

19
00:01:10,798 --> 00:01:15,774
of sentences Sigma is consistent, meaning that one cannot prove phi and not

20
00:01:15,874 --> 00:01:19,632
phi for any formula phi as hard as you try, then there is

21
00:01:19,732 --> 00:01:24,234
at least one model out there which satisfies every formula in Sigma.

22
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,544
We see that this is based on a platonistic

23
00:01:26,644 --> 00:01:30,616
vision of mathematics, where mathematical structures are pre-existing, and

24
00:01:30,716 --> 00:01:33,532
we can characterize them using first order sentences.

25
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,908
If we start to study the general structure of

26
00:01:36,008 --> 00:01:38,583
the models satisfying phi and psi, we might notice

27
00:01:38,683 --> 00:01:41,206
some things in common to all of these structures.

28
00:01:41,266 --> 00:01:47,331
For example we may notice that in none of them do we have aEb and bEa.

29
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:50,309
We can easily see why, since if we did have such

30
00:01:50,409 --> 00:01:54,760
an edge in a transitive and irreflexive structure, then by transitivity

31
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:57,331
we should have a direct path from a to a.

32
00:01:57,466 --> 00:02:01,102
But then the structure is not irreflexive, a contradiction.

33
00:02:01,266 --> 00:02:06,285
So, we see that adding this sentence chi expressing

34
00:02:06,385 --> 00:02:11,906
asymmetry, is redundant, in the sense that Mod(phi, psi,

35
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:15,821
chi) is exactly equal to Mod(phi, psi).

36
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:22,625
We denote this by saying the set phi, psi models chi.

